{"id":"sidon","term":"Sidon","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Fishing; fishery, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:15\">Gen. 10:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:19\">19</a> (A.V. marg., Tzidon; R.V., Zidon); <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 11:21\">Matt. 11:21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 11:22\">22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 6:17\">Luke 6:17</a>. (See ZIDON.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 10:15","Genesis 10:19","Matthew 11:21","Matthew 11:22","Luke 6:17"]}